  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.apache.commons.lang.exception.Nestable

    public class JCSMPErrorResponseException
extends JCSMPOperationException
    JCSMPErrorResponseException is used to capture Solace Message Format (SMF) response codes.

    These types of exceptions are not related to JCSMP. They are most likely caused by the application or the appliance's state.

      • JCSMPErrorResponseException

        public JCSMPErrorResponseException(int responseCode,
                                   String responsePhrase,
                                   String responseBody,
                                   String connectionInfoStr)
        Construct a JCSMPErrorResponseException
        Parameters:
        responseCode - The SMF response code.
        responsePhrase - A short phrase associated with the response code.
        connectionInfoStr - A string that output the connection's information to correlate this exception to a TCP connection
        responseBody - The Content Subscription Management Protocol (CSMP) response message (in XML) itself, if present. Applications must parse this XML content to find the detailed, CSMP-related error conditions.
